                      Shoppers bonanza                    It is that time of year again when the young and the old get ready to usher in the Bengali New Year. An occasion looked forward to with equal enthusiasm by the local Bengali community as well as those from other parts of the country who have made the city their home, it is a day of fun, celebration and bonhomie. As part of its Poila Baishakh celebrations, City Centre New Town and Salt Lake has organised a one-of its-kind shopping festival. The ongoing nine-day fiesta promises to rock the city with its plethora of attractions. The two weekends of the festival are witnessing the best of Bengals handicrafts and sweets in their most traditional forms. Those with a sweet tooth can treat themselves to langcha from Shaktigarh, sharbhaja and sharpuria from Krishnagar, plus specialty sweets like monohara, rabri, malpoa, malai chamcham and a variety of sandesh and rosogolla. Those with a taste for the aesthetic can take their pick from Bankuras dokra, Krishnagars terracotta, Purulias chhau mask, jute from North 24 Parganas and more. Besides shopping, there will be interactive games, competitions and cultural shows, as well as lots of mega prizes on offer for shoppers.                  Event: Shopping festival to celebrate the Bengali New Year When: Till April 18 Where: City Centre, Salt Lake and New Town	                    
